02:57:57,973 --> 02:58:03,717
We do have number nine reports requested follow up presentation on Medford high school action plan.

1261
02:58:03,817 --> 02:58:05,879
Dr. Edward Vincent, superintendent.

1262
02:58:09,591 --> 02:58:24,736
Yes, so the following report is in response to some specific questions that were asked about some of the changes that have taken place at the high school.

1263
02:58:25,716 --> 02:58:36,460
And so there were a lot of questions regarding how long are students waiting to use the restrooms, you know, regarding the,

1264
02:58:39,224 --> 02:58:41,446
the new structures that are in place at the high school.

1265
02:58:42,287 --> 02:58:47,631
And so at lunchtime, we have the cafeteria bathrooms open on all floors.

1266
02:58:49,413 --> 02:59:00,622
And sometimes during that time, due to the volume of students that are eating, a line of three to four students can be there waiting anywhere from two to three minutes.

1267
02:59:02,243 --> 02:59:05,146
But usually the lines are moving fairly quickly.

1268
02:59:06,701 --> 02:59:22,752
As for other periods throughout the day when we don't have a large number of students eating at the same time, I'm not really noticing lines and neither are the administrative teams aware of that.

1269
02:59:24,214 --> 02:59:36,515
At the end of the day, sometimes during period six, there are some students that do request to use the bathrooms at that point in time, but we've been working with them.

1270
02:59:38,166 --> 02:59:38,526
on that.

1271
02:59:39,767 --> 02:59:43,769
The next question that was asked was, how do we know that it's working?

1272
02:59:44,290 --> 02:59:50,933
The two-person maximum for the time being right now, we really feel that it's truly ingrained.

1273
02:59:51,134 --> 02:59:53,295
The students know what the expectation is.

1274
02:59:54,075 --> 03:00:00,359
And so they go in, it's two students at a time outside of all of the larger bathrooms.

1275
03:00:01,420 --> 03:00:10,245
We now have hooks that the students come, they hang their placards and they go into the restroom.

1276
03:00:10,305 --> 03:00:14,788
So at any given time, you can see there are two placards outside.

1277
03:00:14,808 --> 03:00:19,211
And when they come out, they take it and they do that.

1278
03:00:19,291 --> 03:00:22,093
We've added the hooks because it helps to keep track.

1279
03:00:22,993 --> 03:00:31,741
but also we just felt that it was more sanitary to keep the placards outside of the restroom as opposed to inside the restrooms.

1280
03:00:33,583 --> 03:00:39,849
So the next question was, is there evidence that fewer students are outside of the classroom?

1281
03:00:39,989 --> 03:00:43,513
And so the administrators pulled the data

1282
03:00:44,793 --> 03:00:56,359
going back to the beginning of the year, and you can see the noted reduction in cuts that were taking place.

1283
03:00:56,800 --> 03:01:07,985
And so not only do, when you're physically walking the halls, it's completely different experience, but there is hard data to support

1284
03:01:10,266 --> 03:01:11,027
what we're seeing.

1285
03:01:11,547 --> 03:01:14,528
And so we're very, very encouraged by that.

1286
03:01:17,729 --> 03:01:32,034
Moving along, there was a question regarding about the availability in our last meeting and how do we solve this problem in a permanent and sustainable way?

1287
03:01:32,094 --> 03:01:35,896
So we currently have seven building monitors at the high school.

1288
03:01:36,736 --> 03:01:59,866
And so between the cameras being monitored and supervision and support throughout the high school and a designated monitor, at least at the front door, as students and guests or guests come into the building, we do feel that we have a good amount of coverage at the high school.

1289
03:02:02,116 --> 03:02:09,180
in addition to the teachers that signed up to take on some of these additional duties.

1290
03:02:11,281 --> 03:02:22,246
We've encountered a few glitches when we've had coverage where maybe someone was absent and that could be one of the building monitors or if someone was feeling ill, not well.

1291
03:02:22,746 --> 03:02:27,669
So in those cases, we've had to shuffle around

1292
03:02:28,409 --> 03:02:36,732
And if we're short coverage, then the additional administrators will step up and support with additional coverage.

1293
03:02:37,452 --> 03:02:52,157
But again, we do feel at this point in time with the seven monitors that are currently working at the high school, that we feel that it is a manageable number and sustainable.

1294
03:02:53,908 --> 03:02:58,651
So question two, again, was about do we see fewer students roaming the hallways?

1295
03:02:59,172 --> 03:03:14,122
And again, if you refer to the same table that was in question one, yes, it is definitely very obvious and there is a difference.

1296
03:03:16,043 --> 03:03:25,186
And a culture shift is taking place at the high school and we are paying close attention to that.

1297
03:03:26,126 --> 03:03:34,708
So the next question was about the sustainability and the distribution of the school IDs.

1298
03:03:35,308 --> 03:03:44,031
And that which I shared in my last update is an area where we are looking at other options and one of the

1299
03:03:45,131 --> 03:03:57,239
possible suggestions was is there an opportunity to provide electronic IDs or some kind of ID, given that smartphones are everywhere, which we thought was a, you know, excellent suggestion.

1300
03:03:57,259 --> 03:04:04,304
And so we are, you know, willing to look at other options and that could be because again,

1301
03:04:05,525 --> 03:04:17,214
Almost every student has a telephone, so it would just be a question of them potentially being able to show their identification through an electronic ID of some sort.

1302
03:04:17,555 --> 03:04:21,458
So we are trying to explore and look into that as an option.

1303
03:04:23,496 --> 03:04:27,517
Question three was, has there been an increase in the report of bullying?

1304
03:04:28,397 --> 03:04:35,859
And so for the 21-22 school year, there were seven reports of bullying.

1305
03:04:36,739 --> 03:04:43,981
And as of March 15 of 2022, there were two confirmed bullying situations.

1306
03:04:44,941 --> 03:04:47,345
During the school year.

1307
03:04:48,807 --> 03:04:55,577
We have had 10 reports of bullying, bullying, two of them have been confirmed at the high school.

1308
03:04:56,117 --> 03:04:59,362
And so, some of you may wonder why is there a discrepancy.

1309
03:05:01,063 --> 03:05:03,024
With the reports that go forward.

1310
03:05:04,465 --> 03:05:07,266
There could be a variety of solutions.

1311
03:05:08,226 --> 03:05:15,109
There have been restorative circles they have been meetings with students and families where bullying report was.

1312
03:05:16,330 --> 03:05:30,673
submitted but you know the parties came down, came together sat down, had conversations and families chose not to go further with the bullying investigation that happens sometimes.

1313
03:05:31,293 --> 03:05:51,770
We also have some students that a bullying report may have been started for a student and over the course of the investigation and looking into additional supports for those students, that some students may currently be placed in other settings.

1314
03:05:52,191 --> 03:05:55,994
So they received other settings that would provide additional support to them.

1315
03:05:56,694 --> 03:06:08,016
And so in those cases, sometimes the bullying report, because the student was receiving additional supports elsewhere, that that's why that number does not show.

1316
03:06:08,436 --> 03:06:21,579
Also, sometimes when the bullying investigation takes place and it runs its full course, that in the end, it may not be identified or found it to be bullying.

1317
03:06:22,299 --> 03:06:26,441
So that's also another factor.

1318
03:06:26,661 --> 03:06:39,226
But at this point in time for the high school for this year, there are two official confirmed bullying reports that are on record at this point in time.

1319
03:06:41,671 --> 03:06:52,116
The next question was, has there been an audit of appropriateness of prior decisions to ensure that prior decisions were made in compliance with our definitions and policies?

1320
03:06:52,937 --> 03:07:07,564
So the administrative team debriefs regularly, including conversations with our medical staff, our school counselors, engagement specialists, and other building administrative members to ensure

1321
03:07:08,324 --> 03:07:18,150
that appropriate disciplinary measures are being meted out based on the needs of the specific child or student.

1322
03:07:18,810 --> 03:07:23,813
So I can say that not every situation is a one size fits all.

1323
03:07:24,393 --> 03:07:27,575
There are special situations

1324
03:07:28,075 --> 03:07:30,236
that are taken into consideration.

1325
03:07:30,336 --> 03:07:47,124
And so we do collaborate consistently with other members of our team, again, including our medical staff, our counselors, our adjustment specialists, our engagement specialists, our adjustment counselors, school psychologists.

1326
03:07:48,244 --> 03:07:56,128
We bring in many different stakeholders as we look at situations that arise.

1327
03:07:58,427 --> 03:08:01,209
Has the district been responding in a timely way?

1328
03:08:01,870 --> 03:08:05,213
So the district is responding in a timely way.

1329
03:08:05,233 --> 03:08:15,842
The responding administrator follows up with the reporter within 24 to 48 hours or sooner, depending on what the situation is.

1330
03:08:15,902 --> 03:08:24,650
So there is frequent communication between teachers and administrators, and there is a response within 24 to 48 hours.

1331
03:08:26,632 --> 03:08:35,244
And again, decisions are made as soon as practicable based on the details and complexity of what is being reported.

1332
03:08:38,345 --> 03:08:45,310
Question four, when will the handbook be presented to the school committee for review and approval?

1333
03:08:45,911 --> 03:08:54,617
So the high school site council reviews and makes final recommendations at the beginning of May.

1334
03:08:55,838 --> 03:09:01,983
This handbook can be presented to the school committee anytime once the site council review is completed.

1335
03:09:02,643 --> 03:09:12,829
We anticipate bringing an updated version before the committee with revisions by late May to early June of this year.

1336
03:09:12,849 --> 03:09:22,515
And again, the date can be changed at the discretion of the committee, but since it is something that the site councils do look at, there are periodic

1337
03:09:24,417 --> 03:09:32,267
Revisions that may have been done but in light of the greater substantive changes that took place this year.

1338
03:09:33,689 --> 03:09:39,958
We want to be able to just work with the site council and then bring it to the committee by late May early June.

1339
03:09:41,780 --> 03:09:46,924
And the percentage of acknowledgement forms, they have been signed by students and families.

1340
03:09:47,485 --> 03:09:55,511
The hard copies are kept in the assistant principal offices on file.

1341
03:09:55,871 --> 03:10:00,875
So each house has approximately, you know, 400 students, give or take.

1342
03:10:01,455 --> 03:10:05,758
So we are just working on getting those tallies.

1343
03:10:06,459 --> 03:10:11,623
And I can work on getting that to the committee, what the final percentage was.

1344
03:10:13,376 --> 03:10:20,199
How will we know that this worked and what will be or look different if this action was effective?

1345
03:10:20,579 --> 03:10:29,022
So I do feel the hard referral data to the assistant principals has gone down at a significant rate.

1346
03:10:29,802 --> 03:10:35,485
This has allowed them to effectively manage and address student behaviors in a timely fashion.

1347
03:10:36,625 --> 03:10:46,351
Students are reporting during monthly listening sessions that they feel safer now at the high school with the changes that have been made since January.

1348
03:10:47,552 --> 03:10:51,994
Staff are also reporting that they visibly see less roaming in the hallways.

1349
03:10:53,195 --> 03:10:57,418
and students spending more time in their classes.

1350
03:10:58,279 --> 03:11:08,406
Students are following the protocols, using the placards when they need to use the restroom or if they need to go visit one of the other offices.

1351
03:11:09,147 --> 03:11:12,769
So that is really being fully used.

1352
03:11:13,410 --> 03:11:18,553
And the eHaul pass system is also giving us additional accurate data.

1353
03:11:19,614 --> 03:11:21,915
When a student leaves the classroom and returns.

1354
03:11:22,696 --> 03:11:28,419
So, the other piece is the change in tardy check in process.

1355
03:11:29,099 --> 03:11:33,802
It's allowed us to consistently see which students are coming to school late in real time.

1356
03:11:34,882 --> 03:11:52,074
And I think all of these changes have significantly contributed to more calm and greater consistency and clarity around expectations at the high school.

1357
03:11:52,534 --> 03:11:57,998
So I just wanted to make sure that I responded to all the questions that I had received.

1358
03:11:58,558 --> 03:11:58,898
Thank you.

1359
03:11:59,219 --> 03:12:00,399
Thank you, Dr. Edward Vincent.

1360
03:12:00,980 --> 03:12:01,280
Thank you.

